    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DAEWOO AUDIT DEEPENS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>South Korean government extends audit of conglomerate Daewoo Group after auditors found fresh evidence of further false accounting (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Auditors at the Daewoo Group found evidence of further false accounting, leading the South Korean government to extend an audit. Around 23 trillion won ($21 billion) out of the conglomerate's total assets of 80 trillion to 90 trillion won has been confirmed to have been hidden in various accounts and manipulated, said Chung Ki Young, an official at the financial watchdog agency in charge of auditing Daewoo's financial records.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len (NYT)</p>
      </block>
